---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Support â€” GitSorted">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Support</h1>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For support requests, bug reports, or feature suggestions, email us at
          <a href="mailto:support@gitsorted.app" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline">support@gitsorted.app</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-1">Where is my data stored?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">All data is stored locally on your device as git repositories. Items are plain JSON files inside each repository. Nothing is sent to our servers.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-1">What happens if I delete the app?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Local data is removed with the app. If you have synced lists to a remote git server, that data remains on the remote until you delete it there.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-1">Which git providers are supported?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, Gitea, AWS CodeCommit, Azure Repos, and any self-hosted git server accessible via HTTPS.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-1">How do I restore my Pro purchase?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Open Settings in the app and tap "Restore Purchases." Your purchase is tied to your Apple ID or Google account and can be restored on any device.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-1">Can I request a refund?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Refunds are handled by Apple or Google. Visit <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline">reportaproblem.apple.com</a> for App Store purchases.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
